I sometimes stay with my girlfriend when I go back home just to have a little privacy. We plan to get married in December. She is the one who is currently supporting me so that I can go back to school.

In April, I graduated with a certificate in refrigeration and air conditioning. My transport costs for the past year and a half have been totally paid for by my girlfriend. There are just some little things here and there that I haven’t been able to attend to due to lack of funding.

One time, our relationship got so strained that we were getting phone calls from her fiancé about money. That was really stressful, but we talked it through and the relationship is so much stronger because of our conversations.”

What he’s learning at UNIMAID

“I started studying computer science at the University of Maiduguri just three weeks ago, but there was time when my cooking instructor suggested I get a job as a dishwasher in a restaurant. So I contacted the owner, who agreed to pay me ₦5,000 a month, ₦2,000 less than the normal dishwashing income in his restaurant. I told her that I could not accept such wage, despite the fact that there was a strike at UNIMAID at that time. So, she finally agreed to pay me ₦10,000 a month
